<HEAD>With PM-World's Richest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the 119 individuals or families outside
the United States who have personal fortunes exceeding $1 billion,
according to the July 25 issue of Forbes magazine.
   Forbes did not report specific amounts for each family, only
grouping them in general categories of wealth.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>Over $10 Billion</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Taikichiro Mori, Japan, real estate.
   Yoshiaki Tsutsumi, Japan, transportation, hotels, leisure
industry.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>Over $5 Billion</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Ramon Areces, Spain, retailing.
   Kenneth Cole Irving, Canada, oil distribution, paper, land.
   Eitaro Itoyama, Japan, leisure industry.
   Reichmann family (Paul, Albert, Ralph), Canada, real estate.
   Shin Kyuk-ho, South Korea, candy, hotels, real estate.
   Kenneth Roy Thomson, Canada, publishing, retailing.
   Tsai Wan-lin, Taiwan, insurance, construction.
   Kitaro Watanabe, Japan, real estate, hotels.
   Haruhiko Yoshimoto, Japan, real estate.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>Over $2 Billion</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Giovanni Agnelli family, Italy, autos, investments.
   Brenninkmeyer family, West Germany, retailing.
   Friedrich Karl Flick, West Germany, finance.
   Garza Sada family, Mexico, beer, steel, packaging.
   Pablo Escobar Gaviria, Colombia, illegal drugs.
   Gerald Cavendish Grosvenor, Britain, real estate.
   Ervian Haub, West Germany, supermarkets.
   Henkel family, West Germany, consumer products.
   Ferruzzi family, Italy, agricultural conglomerate.
   Masatohsi Ito, Japan, retailing.
   Yohachiro Iwasaki, Japan, logging, real estate, leisure industry.
   Ingvar Kamprad, Sweden, furniture retailing.
   Shigeru Kobayashi, Japan, real estate.
   Liem Sioe Liong, Indonesia, finance, trade, manufacturing.
   Seijiro Matsuoka, Japan, real estate.
   Konosuke Matsushita, Japan, electronics.
   Reinhard Mohn, West Germany, publishing.
   Kenkichi Nakajima, Japan, gambling machines.
   Ochoa family, Colombia, illegal drugs.
   Rudolf August Oetker family, West Germany, food, brewing.
   Yoneichi Otani, Japan, hotels.
   Quandt family, West Germany, autos, industry.
   Al-Rajhi family, Saudi Arabia, money changing.
   Rausing family (Hans, Gad), Sweden, liquids packaging.
   Kiyoshi Sagawa, Japan, delivery service.
   David Sainsbury, Britain, supermarkets.
   Keizo Saji, Japan, liquor.
   Kichinosuke Sasaki, Japan, real estate.
   Schlumberger family, France, oil services.
   Stephan Schmidheiny, Switzerland, industry.
   Rinji Shino, Japan, real estate, leisure industry.
   Hirotomo Takei, Japan, publishing, real estate.
   Takenaka family, Japan, construction.
   Vestey family (Samuel, Edmund), Britain, meatpacking.
   Von Finck family (Wilhelm, August), West Germany, finance.
   Von Oppenheim family, West Germany, banking.
   Y.C. Wang, Taiwan, plastics.
   Werhahn family, West Germany, retailing, banking.
   Weston family (Garry, Galen), Canada, supermarkets.
   Tadao Yoshida, Japan, zipper manufacturing, building materials.
